article.headline: CS Northridge 82, Cal Poly 77
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Mike Efevberha scored 20 points off the bench including six free throws in the final 31.2 seconds to lead Cal State Northridge to an 82-77 victory Thursday over Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. Efevberha had his ninth 20-point game of the season and helped the Matadors (11-15, 4-9 Big West) stop a three-game losing streak. Cal Poly (9-17, 7-6) made four 3-pointers in the final 33.8 seconds and fouled after each one. Efevberha received the inbound passes, took the fouls and made all six of his free throws, allowing Cal Poly to get no closer than three points. Calvin Chitwood scored 13 of his season-high 19 points in the second half for Northridge, including eight in the last six minutes. He also had a game-high 12 rebounds. Despite the loss, Cal Poly secured a top-four seed and a first-round bye in next week's Big West tournament. Trae Clark scored a career-best 20 points off the bench for Cal Poly, and Derek Stockalper had 15 points and 10 rebounds.
